  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Standardize Typography and Visual Design for Single News Page\n\nUpdate the single news page to match the typography, spacing, and visual design patterns used throughout the rest of the application, creating a cohesive and polished user experience.\n\nRequirements:\n- Audit typography on single news page and compare with other pages (font families, sizes, weights, line heights)\n- Apply consistent heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3) matching site-wide standards\n- Align text colors, link styles, and text formatting with global design system\n- Standardize spacing and layout (margins, padding, content width, white space)\n- Ensure visual elements (images, cards, buttons, dividers) match design patterns used elsewhere\n- Improve readability with appropriate line length, paragraph spacing, and contrast ratios\n- Add consistent styling for metadata (author, date, categories, tags)\n- Verify responsive behavior matches other pages across device sizes\n- Ensure accessibility standards are maintained (proper heading structure, color contrast, focus states)",
